{#-
  AspectRatio — box wrapper that maintains a defined aspect ratio for its
  inner content (typically an image, video, iframe, or canvas).

  Pure CSS via the modern `aspect-ratio` property (Baseline 2022). Zero
  Stimulus, zero polyfill — every browser the kit supports has it.

  The wrapper applies `inline-size: 100%` (fills its parent's inline-axis)
  and `aspect-ratio: var(--cremona-aspect-ratio)` so the block-size derives
  from the inline-size. Inner `<img>` / `<video>` / `<iframe>` are sized
  to fill the box with `object-fit: cover` by default.

  Two usage patterns:

  1. {% embed %} block — the canonical Twig way:

       {% embed '@cremona/components/aspect-ratio/aspect-ratio.html.twig'
                with { ratio: '16/9' } %}
         {% block content %}
           <img src="/cover.jpg" alt="…">
         {% endblock %}
       {% endembed %}

  2. Raw HTML — the CSS contract works on `<div class="cremona-aspect-ratio"
     style="--cremona-aspect-ratio: 16/9">`:

       <div class="cremona-aspect-ratio" style="--cremona-aspect-ratio: 16/9">
         <img src="/cover.jpg" alt="…">
       </div>

  Parameters:
    ratio        (string, optional) — CSS aspect-ratio value (e.g. '16/9',
                                      '4/3', '1/1', '3/2', '1.91/1' for OG,
                                      '9/16' portrait, '21/9' cinemascope).
                                      Default: '16/9'.
    fit          (string, optional) — object-fit on the inner element:
                                      cover (default) | contain | fill | none | scale-down
    className    (string, optional)

  Block `content` (required when embedding):
    The inner element (img, video, iframe, picture, or any block) that
    inherits the aspect-ratio's block-size.
-#}

{%- set ratio     = ratio     | default('16/9') -%}
{%- set fit       = fit       | default('cover') -%}
{%- set className = className | default('') -%}

{%- set _classes = ['cremona-aspect-ratio'] -%}
{%- if fit != 'cover' -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge(['cremona-aspect-ratio--fit-' ~ fit]) -%}{%- endif -%}
{%- if className -%}{%- set _classes = _classes | merge([className]) -%}{%- endif -%}

<div class="{{ _classes | join(' ') }}" style="--cremona-aspect-ratio: {{ ratio }};">
  {%- block content -%}{%- endblock -%}
</div>
